# AI SDK and agentic actions — check docs first

Before implementing **custom functions**, **tools**, or **agentic behavior**:

1. **Check the official docs first**: [AI SDK documentation](https://ai-sdk.dev/docs/)
2. Prefer built-in or documented patterns over one-off custom code.

## When this applies

- Adding or changing tools, agents, or LLM-driven flows
- Implementing loops, tool calling, streaming, or message handling
- Using MCP, providers, or model options

## What to do

- **Agents**: See [Agents](https://ai-sdk.dev/docs/agents/overview), [Building Agents](https://ai-sdk.dev/docs/agents/building-agents), [Loop Control](https://ai-sdk.dev/docs/agents/loop-control)
- **Tools**: See [Tools](https://ai-sdk.dev/docs/foundations/tools), [Tool Calling](https://ai-sdk.dev/docs/ai-sdk-core/tools-and-tool-calling)
- **MCP**: See [MCP](https://ai-sdk.dev/docs/ai-sdk-core/mcp-tools) and reference for `createMCPClient`
- **Streaming / UI**: See [Streaming](https://ai-sdk.dev/docs/foundations/streaming) and [AI SDK UI](https://ai-sdk.dev/docs/ai-sdk-ui/overview)

Only implement custom logic when the docs do not cover the use case or when the task explicitly requires a custom approach.
